Once I have both tables loaded, I need to join them based on the employee_id. Since only employees present in both tables should appear in the result, I'll perform an inner join. In data.table, this can be done using the [ ] operator with the join condition. So, offices[i$employee_id == j$employee_id, ...], but more efficiently, I can use .(employee_id) to specify the columns.

After joining, I should have a new table called 'result' that includes employee_id, work_address, and home_address. Finally, I need to write this result to a CSV file named 'result.csv'. The write.csv function will handle this, but again, specifying sep = ',' ensures that commas are used as delimiters.

